{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"We live in a time of fear,"},{"time":3800,"text":"and our response to fear\ncan either be to contract"},{"time":7200,"text":"and attempt to guard ourselves"},{"time":10000,"text":"or to extend ourselves,\nhold on to each other,"},{"time":13160,"text":"and face our fears together."},{"time":16160,"text":"What is your instinct?"},{"time":18680,"text":"What do you see more of in the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22240,"text":"The problem with the first approach"},{"time":24240,"text":"is that in our mounting isolation,"},{"time":26600,"text":"we divide ourselves from others."},{"time":29240,"text":"Our sense of isolation grows,"},{"time":31680,"text":"because our imagination\ngoes into overdrive"},{"time":33840,"text":"about the people and the spaces\nthat we no longer engage with."},{"time":37400,"text":"Our sense of otherness grows,\nand we lose empathy."},{"time":42560,"text":"Today I'm going to tell you\nabout a group of people"},{"time":45000,"text":"that took the global\nchallenge of terrorism"},{"time":47160,"text":"and began creating spaces\nwhere strangers connect in solidarity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52920,"text":"My own obsession with what I see\nas irrational divisions began as a child."},{"time":57840,"text":"As a fourth-generation\nKenyan Muslim of Indian origin,"},{"time":62040,"text":"it bothered me that in four generations,"},{"time":64000,"text":"there wasn't a single\nmarriage in my family"},{"time":66080,"text":"outside of my small religious community."},{"time":68880,"text":"And I wondered what that was about."},{"time":71600,"text":"Was it fear?"},{"time":73400,"text":"Was it racism?"},{"time":76240,"text":"Was it cultural preservation?"},{"time":78760,"text":"Did it have something\nto do with colonialism?"},{"time":82240,"text":"Certainly, we didn't share a lot\nof the same public spaces with others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87680,"text":"These divisions bothered me deeply,\nand they drove my career choices."},{"time":92400,"text":"When I was 20, the US embassies\nin Kenya and Tanzania were bombed."},{"time":99080,"text":"A year later, I was on my way\nto the Middle East"},{"time":101360,"text":"to study conflict resolution."},{"time":103880,"text":"And then from that point on,"},{"time":105280,"text":"it wasn't very hard for me\nto find insecure environments to work in,"},{"time":108840,"text":"because the world was quickly shifting"},{"time":110720,"text":"in what we now know\nas the time of terrorism."},{"time":113920,"text":"I was in Washington, DC\nwhen 9/11 happened,"},{"time":117200,"text":"and then I moved back home\nto Kenya to work with refugees"},{"time":120680,"text":"and then later worked in Pakistan"},{"time":122840,"text":"and in Afghanistan."},{"time":126120,"text":"In all of these places, what I noticed"},{"time":128800,"text":"was how important physical spaces are"},{"time":131360,"text":"to making us feel safe"},{"time":133760,"text":"and well"},{"time":135080,"text":"and like we belong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137760,"text":"In 2013, I came back home\nto Nairobi from Afghanistan."},{"time":142640,"text":"Al-Shabaab operatives\nhad besieged Westgate shopping center,"},{"time":145800,"text":"killing 67 people\nin a day of utter horror."},{"time":152040,"text":"Soon after that,"},{"time":153960,"text":"I could see how Nairobi\nwas beginning to change,"},{"time":156440,"text":"and it was beginning to feel\nmore like the fear and terror-weary"},{"time":161400,"text":"and war-torn cities that I had worked in."},{"time":165240,"text":"And Nairobi continues to grow\nin fear-driven ways."},{"time":169320,"text":"We see more walls, more barriers,"},{"time":171880,"text":"more security."},{"time":174000,"text":"And like other parts of the world,"},{"time":175680,"text":"we are experiencing\nan erosion of human connection."},{"time":180320,"text":"Divisions along\nreligious lines are deepening,"},{"time":183440,"text":"and we're doubting more and more\nhow much we have in common."},{"time":188600,"text":"We are at a pivotal time"},{"time":189920,"text":"when we need to restore\nour confidence in humanity"},{"time":193480,"text":"and stand boldly and visibly together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197880,"text":"So in 2014, I brought together\na group of people in Nairobi"},{"time":200680,"text":"to figure out what to do:"},{"time":202680,"text":"public intellectuals, diplomats,\nartists, development workers."},{"time":208520,"text":"And the group articulated\nour challenge as threefold:"},{"time":213000,"text":"one, to reclaim the city\nfrom the narrative of terrorism"},{"time":216960,"text":"and back into the hands\nof the people that live there;"},{"time":220200,"text":"two, introduce a language\nbeyond race, tribe or religion"},{"time":224280,"text":"that would help us\ntranscend our differences;"},{"time":227680,"text":"and three, provide a gesture\nthat would help restore empathy"},{"time":232240,"text":"and conversation and trust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236520,"text":"One of the people in this group\nwas an artist and architect,"},{"time":239520,"text":"Yazmany Arboleda."},{"time":242040,"text":"He and I have collaborated\nin other parts of the world"},{"time":244840,"text":"over many years."},{"time":246440,"text":"He has a history"},{"time":248000,"text":"of disrupting urban environments"},{"time":250560,"text":"and making strangers connect"},{"time":252240,"text":"in incredible, beautiful\nand spectacular ways."},{"time":256880,"text":"He had an idea."},{"time":258640,"text":"The idea was to unite people\nof different faiths"},{"time":261800,"text":"by getting them to paint\neach other's houses of worship,"},{"time":265000,"text":"mosques, temples, synagogues, churches,"},{"time":268720,"text":"paint them yellow"},{"time":270680,"text":"in the name of love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274160,"text":"By focusing on icons of faith,"},{"time":277520,"text":"we would get people to reexamine\nthe true essence of their faith,"},{"time":281600,"text":"the common belief that we share\nin kindness, generosity and friendship."},{"time":286800,"text":"By creating pathways\nbetween houses of worship"},{"time":289840,"text":"within one neighborhood,"},{"time":291480,"text":"we would create islands of stability"},{"time":293400,"text":"and networks of people"},{"time":294840,"text":"that could withstand threats."},{"time":298160,"text":"And neighbors, by picking up\na paintbrush with other neighbors,"},{"time":302720,"text":"would engage not just with their heads"},{"time":304760,"text":"but with their hands\nand with their hearts."},{"time":308320,"text":"And the painted buildings would become\nsculptures in the landscape"},{"time":311480,"text":"that speak of people\nfrom very different backgrounds"},{"time":314160,"text":"that stand together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317520,"text":"We'd call the project \"Colour in Faith.\""},{"time":320400,"text":"We loved the idea and we immediately\nbegan approaching houses of worship:"},{"time":324480,"text":"churches, temples, mosques, synagogues."},{"time":327280,"text":"Door to door, we went\nto more than 60 rabbis,"},{"time":329960,"text":"imams, pastors and priests."},{"time":333160,"text":"As you can imagine,"},{"time":334640,"text":"bringing these communities together"},{"time":336360,"text":"when prejudices are reinforced\nby a global pandemic of fear"},{"time":339600,"text":"is not easy."},{"time":340880,"text":"It was complicated."},{"time":343560,"text":"We were confronted\nwith the hierarchy of decision-making"},{"time":346240,"text":"within religious establishments."},{"time":348520,"text":"For example, with Catholic churches,"},{"time":351040,"text":"we were told that the archbishop\nwould have to make the decision."},{"time":354360,"text":"And so we wrote a letter\nto the archbishop."},{"time":356480,"text":"We wrote a letter to the Vatican."},{"time":358840,"text":"We're still waiting to hear back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362320,"text":"And with other houses of worship,"},{"time":364400,"text":"we were told that the patrons,\nthe people that pay for the building"},{"time":367600,"text":"and the construction\nand the painting of the buildings"},{"time":370160,"text":"would have to make a decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"And then we came head-to-head"},{"time":374480,"text":"with the long legacy\nof missionary and donor dependence"},{"time":377200,"text":"that so impedes\nunconditional civic action,"},{"time":380520,"text":"and we learned this the hard way."},{"time":382440,"text":"There was one community"},{"time":384040,"text":"that in our repeated conversations\nwould keep asking us"},{"time":387400,"text":"to appreciate them."},{"time":389760,"text":"And so we would keep going back"},{"time":391800,"text":"and telling them that we appreciate them,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and of course,"},{"time":395840,"text":"if we didn't appreciate them,\nwe wouldn't be here."},{"time":401080,"text":"And then we learned\npainfully late in the game"},{"time":403600,"text":"that the word \"appreciation\"\nis code for getting paid to participate."},{"time":409480,"text":"And so we challenged them"},{"time":412600,"text":"and we asked the question,"},{"time":414440,"text":"\"So what will it cost?"},{"time":416640,"text":"How much could we pay you?"},{"time":419760,"text":"And if we pay for your faith,\nis it really faith?\""},{"time":423840,"text":"We started the project\nasking the question,"},{"time":426480,"text":"\"Where does your faith live?\""},{"time":428680,"text":"And here we found ourselves\nasking the question,"},{"time":430960,"text":"\"How much does your faith cost?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":434280,"text":"But the most difficult issue\nwas the perceived risk of standing apart."},{"time":438680,"text":"We had one synagogue\nthat flat-out refused to participate"},{"time":442600,"text":"because it feared\ndrawing attention to itself"},{"time":444840,"text":"and becoming a target."},{"time":447000,"text":"Similarly, we had a mosque\nthat also feared becoming a target."},{"time":451600,"text":"And these fears are justified."},{"time":455480,"text":"And yet, there were 25 houses of worship\nthat pledged to participate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466760,"text":"These bold leaders took the gesture\nand reinforced it with their own meaning."},{"time":471280,"text":"For some, it was to tell the world\nthat they're not terrorists."},{"time":474920,"text":"For others, it was to welcome people\nthrough their doors to ask questions."},{"time":479640,"text":"And for some, it was to bridge the gap"},{"time":481520,"text":"between the older\nand the younger generation,"},{"time":483680,"text":"which by the way is something that\nmany faiths are grappling with right now."},{"time":488200,"text":"And for some it was simply\nto build neighborhood solidarity"},{"time":492040,"text":"in advance of feared election violence."},{"time":495880,"text":"When asked why yellow,"},{"time":497440,"text":"one imam beautifully said,"},{"time":499720,"text":"\"Yellow is the color of the sun."},{"time":502400,"text":"The sun shines on us all equally."},{"time":504960,"text":"It does not discriminate.\""},{"time":507480,"text":"He and others spread the word\nthrough their congregations"},{"time":510200,"text":"and over the radio."},{"time":511440,"text":"Municipal government officials\nstepped forward and helped"},{"time":514159,"text":"with permits and with convening\ncivil society organizations."},{"time":518360,"text":"A paint company donated\na thousand liters of yellow paint"},{"time":522000,"text":"mixed especially for us\nin what they now call \"optimistic yellow.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":525640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532040,"text":"And a poetry collective\njoined forces with a university"},{"time":535320,"text":"and hosted a series of tweet chats"},{"time":537600,"text":"that challenged the nation\non issues of faith,"},{"time":539800,"text":"our faith not just\nin the context of religion,"},{"time":542480,"text":"but our faith in politicians\nand tribe and nation,"},{"time":546200,"text":"our faith in the older generation\nand in the younger generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551360,"text":"And then Colour in Faith\nwas launched at a gallery event"},{"time":555240,"text":"that invited an incredible mix\nof gallerygoers"},{"time":558760,"text":"and religious leaders\nand artists and businesspeople."},{"time":563560,"text":"Already, even before\npicking up a paintbrush,"},{"time":566240,"text":"we had accomplished so much\nof the conversation and connection"},{"time":570480,"text":"that we had hoped for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"And then we began to paint."},{"time":577920,"text":"Muslims stood by Christians"},{"time":580080,"text":"and atheists and agnostics and Hindus"},{"time":583320,"text":"and painted a mosque yellow."},{"time":590040,"text":"And then they all came together again\nand painted a church yellow,"},{"time":595120,"text":"and then another mosque,"},{"time":597240,"text":"and then another church."},{"time":599840,"text":"Poets and musicians\nperformed while we painted."},{"time":603160,"text":"We painted in Nairobi,"},{"time":605320,"text":"and then we painted in Mombasa."},{"time":608840,"text":"The local and international press\ndid features on Colour in Faith"},{"time":612720,"text":"in English and French and Swahili"},{"time":615760,"text":"and Spanish and Somali."},{"time":618400,"text":"CNN highlighted Colour in Faith\nas a way of bringing communities together."},{"time":625520,"text":"And our social media platforms lit up,"},{"time":628400,"text":"connecting more and more people."},{"time":630960,"text":"And these neighbors\ncontinued to stay in touch."},{"time":634840,"text":"There are some that are pursuing\npolitics with a platform of peace,"},{"time":638480,"text":"and we have communities\nas far as Argentina and the US"},{"time":641560,"text":"and as close as Mali and Rwanda"},{"time":643840,"text":"that are asking for our help."},{"time":645680,"text":"And we would love to help."},{"time":647960,"text":"It's our dream that this project,\nthis idea, spreads across the world,"},{"time":652160,"text":"with or without our support."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655480,"text":"Colour in Faith is literally highlighting\nthose who mean well in yellow."},{"time":661000,"text":"Colour in Faith is binding\nneighborhoods together,"},{"time":663560,"text":"and it's our hope\nthat when threats come knocking,"},{"time":666080,"text":"they will collectively\nsift fact from rumor"},{"time":668480,"text":"and stand in solidarity."},{"time":671320,"text":"We've proven that the human family\ncan come together and send a message"},{"time":675000,"text":"far brighter and more powerful"},{"time":677400,"text":"than the voices of those\nthat wish to do us harm."},{"time":681320,"text":"Though fear is infectious,"},{"time":683040,"text":"we are showing that so is hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686840,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}